ADDITIONAL RESEARCH & COMPLIANCE CLAUSES:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. INTENDED USE AND RESTRICTIONS:
The Software is a research and demonstration tool of the Proof of Concept (PoC) 
class, developed solely for academic research, validation of network stack 
conformance to the RFC 9000 (QUIC) standard, and security auditing. Use of this 
Software is permitted EXCLUSIVELY on isolated test benches, within IT infrastructure 
owned by the user, or with the express prior written consent of the target system owner.

2. LEGAL STATUS:
This Software is a testing tool and does not contain functionalities for unauthorized 
access, destruction, blocking, or modification of computer information. The Software 
generates minimal-length test UDP datagrams to verify the resilience of state machines 
against atypical data structures. It is not designed or intended to cause system 
failures, disruptions, or denial of service.

3. USER RESPONSIBILITY:
The end-user assumes all risk and full legal responsibility for compliance with 
applicable local and international laws (including cybercrime and critical 
infrastructure protection acts) when running this Software. Deployment or utilization 
of this Software constitutes the user's unconditional acceptance of this agreement.

